data.enText: refusing to change your opinions, way of behaving, etc. when other people try to persuade you to; showing this

data.chText: 他的犟劲儿一上来，简直执拗得要命！
data.enText: He can be very obstinate when he wants to be!

data.chText: 她对他们的请求坚辞不从
data.enText: her obstinate refusal to comply with their request

data.chText: 棘手的；难以去除的；难以对付的
data.enText: difficult to get rid of or deal with
He obstinately refused to consider the future.

simple_means.memory_skill: ob 逆 + stin 站，立 + ate 有…性质的 →〔和别人〕反着站 → 顽固的

ex.chText: 她的许多雇员发现她个性固执。
ex.enText: Many of her employees find her inflexible.

ex.chText: 那家公司在这个问题上丝毫不肯变通。
ex.enText: The company is completely inflexible on this matter.

synonyms.bx: 多指人、机构等行事死板的，不愿意改变观念、决定、方法等。

ex.chText: 格伦年轻、任性，但骨子里是个好人。
ex.enText: Glenn is young and very headstrong, but he is a good man underneath it all.

ex.chText: 他是个任性的孩子，总是惹麻烦。
ex.enText: He was a headstrong kid, always getting into trouble.

synonyms.bx: 指人执拗任性的，强调行事偏执，不肯听从劝告。

ex.chText: 这姑娘有的时候会非常固执。
ex.enText: This girl can be obstinate at times.

ex.chText: 我的朋友非常顽固，而且又铁了心，是不会放弃的。
ex.enText: My friend is obstinate and determined, and will not give up.

synonyms.bx: 指人固执己见的，喜欢我行我素，不愿改变主意、行事方法等，常含贬义。

ex.enText: Why is the captain so stubborn/obstinate?
He was too stubborn/obstinate to admit that there was a problem.

synonyms.bx: 词义同obstinate，可换用，也常含贬义。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：顽固的，固执的

example: he obstinates himself against all rational arguments
an obstinate child with a violent temper

tr: tenaciously unwilling or marked by tenacious unwillingness to yield

value.def: If you describe someone as obstinate, you are being critical of them because they are very determined to do what they want, and refuse to change their mind or be persuaded to do something else.

example.ex: He is obstinate and determined and will not give up...
example.tran: 他非常顽固，而且又铁了心，是不会放弃的。

example.ex: She was a wicked and obstinate child.
example.tran: 她是个淘气又执拗的孩子。

example.ex: I stayed obstinately in my room, sitting by the telephone...
example.tran: 我执意呆在房间里，坐在电话机旁边。

example.ex: Smith obstinately refused to carry out the order.
example.tran: 史密斯我行我素，拒不执行命令。

example.ex: I might have become a dangerous man with all that stubbornness and obstinacy built into me.
example.tran: 我若是养就了那种根深蒂固的犟脾气，也许就成了危险分子。

value.def: You can describe things as obstinate when they are difficult to move, change, or destroy.

example.ex: ...rusted farm equipment strewn among the obstinate weeds.
example.tran: 扔在恣意蔓生的杂草丛中的锈迹斑斑的农具

value.tran: 难以移动的；难以改变的；难以消除的

example.ex: ...the door of the shop which obstinately stayed closed when he tried to push it open.
example.tran: 他怎么使劲也推不开的店门
